@TechReport{Lixfeld,
  author   = {Peter Lixfeld},
  title    = {Profile, Contour and Flatness Control with CVCplus® Technology},
  abstract = {INTRODUCTION
SMS Siemag’s invention of Continuously Variable Crown (CVC) rolls in the 1980s was a major breakthrough in profile and flatness
control. Traditional methods, based on rolling force distribution, work roll coolant patterns, or backup rolls with modifiable shapes,
provided only a limited range of profile control while attempting to deliver acceptable flatness. Because roll shapes change during
rolling and between passes, simultaneous optimal profile and flatness control requires changes to the gap profile between work rolls of
various magnitude: drastic changes from pass to pass, incremental changes during a pass, and gradual changes from piece to piece.
CVCplus® technology, comprised of specially shaped CVC work rolls and backup rolls, work roll shifting, work roll bending and an
automation system known as Profile, Contour and Flatness Control (PCFC), is well-suited to simultaneously achieve profile and
flatness, two objectives that normally counteract one other, during a long and flexibly scheduled rolling campaign. In the multi-stand
hot strip mills this technology also provides a strip contour control without compromising the quality of a profile and flatness control.
This article will compare CVCplus® technology with conventional methods of profile and flatness control, starting with basic
definitions, following with outlining conventional control methods and then delving into the major improvements the CVCplus®
makes on them. It will first explore how the use of CVC rolls impacts the ability to control the gap between work rolls and
consequently control of the profile, contour and flatness of rolled metal. Next, it will focus on work roll shifting and bending
mechanisms, and will then describe the role and major functions of the accompanying PCFC automation system. This article
highlights the unquestionable benefits that CVCplus® technology brings to the hundreds of modified and new mill stands – both hot
and cold, and both steel and aluminum – in which it has been installed throughout the world


SUMMARY
CVCplus® technology provides superior tools for simultaneous profile (crown) and flatness control. This technology, comprised of
mechanical and automation inventions derived and implemented by SMS Siemag for more than thirty years, has come to be a mature,
well-proven solution to these essential quality requirements that, with conventional methods, could not be achieved.
An example of plates produced by the wide plate mill with CVCplus® is shown in Figure 27.
18
By essentially rendering obsolete the tradeoff between profile control and flatness control, CVCplus® technology has opened up a new
range of flexibility, both in terms of rolling campaign schedules and product mix. Longer and more flexible rolling campaigns,
together with a more extensive product mix, translates , in the long run, to increased productivity, decreased costs of operation, and
high product quality, all of which serve to increase the bottom line in the present as well as positioning a mill in an excellent position
to look toward the future.
Admittedly, CVCplus® technology comes with an initial cost. It may require additional outlays in new machinery and technology, but
the long-run advantages to productivity, operational costs, and product quality are clear. Moreover, the self-adaptive control
mechanisms of the PCFC assure the stability of the system and practically eliminate the need for operator intervention, and virtually
no maintenance is required.
CVCplus® technology is a universal solution not restricted to one specific mill layout, type of mill stand, or processed metal.
CVCplus® technology has been widely accepted around the world, and hundreds of mills are benefiting from it today.},
  file     = {:Lixfeld/Lixfeld.pdf:PDF},
  keywords = {CVCplus® Technology, Profile Control, Flatness Control, Contour Control, Roll Shifting, Roll Bending, Automation System, Productivity, Operational Costs, Product Quality, PCFC, CVCplus® Technologie, Profilregelung, Planheitsregelung, Konturregelung, Walzenverschiebung, Walzenbiegung},
}

